# Database Conventions

## Migration rules
- Files: `supabase/migrations/NNN_descriptive_name.sql` (zero-padded, e.g. `008_`)
- **All migrations must be idempotent**: use `IF NOT EXISTS`, `DROP … IF EXISTS`, `CREATE OR REPLACE`
- Never DROP columns or tables in migrations — add new columns, deprecate old ones
- Run via: `npm run migrate` (requires Supabase CLI linked)
- Generate types after schema changes: `npm run types`

## Key tables
| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `profiles` | Extended user data (role, status, full_name, phone) |
| `products` | Products with cost, pricing, tiers, media, availability |
| `orders` | COD affiliate orders |
| `wholesale_cart_items` | Cart for wholesale buyers |
| `wholesale_orders` | Confirmed wholesale orders |
| `wholesale_order_items` | Line items per wholesale order |
| `commissions` | Commission records per delivered order |
| `payouts` | Affiliate payout batches |
| `order_proofs` | Attachment-ready proof schema (bank receipts, delivery proofs) |

## Product schema highlights
```sql
availability_type   text  -- 'local_stock' | 'import_on_demand'
origin_detail       text  -- 'locally_produced' | 'imported_but_in_morocco_stock'
affiliate_enabled   bool  -- false when import_on_demand
purchase_currency   text  -- 'MAD' | 'USD' | 'AED' only
media               jsonb -- [{url, type}] type: 'image'|'video'|'telegram_link'|'external_link'
confirmation_fee_mad numeric -- default 10
packaging_fee_mad   numeric -- default 10
delivery_fee_mad    numeric -- default 0, set per product
wholesale_tiers     jsonb  -- [{min_qty, max_qty?, price_per_unit}]
```

## RLS pattern
Every table has RLS enabled. Pattern:
- Admins: full access via `my_role() = 'admin'`
- Affiliates: read own rows via `affiliate_id = auth.uid()`
- Wholesalers: read own cart/orders via `buyer_id = auth.uid()`
- Public: read active+approved products, insert COD orders (anonymous allowed)

## Triggers
- `handle_updated_at()` — auto-sets updated_at on UPDATE
- `handle_new_user()` — creates profile row on auth.users INSERT
- `handle_order_delivered()` — creates commission record when order status → 'delivered'
  - Guard: only if `commission_amount > 0` AND `affiliate_id IS NOT NULL`

## RPCs
- `reserve_stock(product_id, qty)` — decrements stock with FOR UPDATE lock
- `restore_stock(product_id, qty)` — increments stock (on cancellation)

## Commission flow
```
order confirmed → commission_amount recorded on order
order delivered → handle_order_delivered trigger → INSERT into commissions (status='pending')
admin approves → commissions.status = 'approved'
admin pays → commissions.status = 'paid', payouts table updated
```
